The paper deals with the capacity regions of a two-user Gaussian multiple access channel (GMAC) with different multiple access schemes. This involves information theory (cs.IT) and communication theory (cs.COMM). The paper also discusses the impact of power and bandwidth constraints on the capacity regions, which falls under the category of signal processing (cs.SI) and networking (cs.NI). Finally, the paper compares different multiple access schemes and their performance, which can be considered as a machine learning (cs.LG) problem.
